meta.description: Very fast version of the Gemma-7b-it is a instruction fine-tuned LLM, lightweight open model from Google DeepMind that offers state-of-the-art performance for natural language processing tasks, trained on a diverse dataset with rigorous safety and bias mitigation measures.

Very fast version of the Gemma-2-9b-it is a instruction fine-tuned LLM, lightweight open model from Google DeepMind that offers state-of-the-art performance for natural language processing tasks, trained on a diverse dataset with rigorous safety and bias mitigation measures.
Very fast version of the Llama 3.1 that is a new state-of-the-art model from Meta here available in 70B.
Very fast version of the Llama 3.1 that is a new state-of-the-art model from Meta here available in 8B.
Very fast version of Mixtral 8x7B that is a popular high-quality sparse Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) model ideal for text summarization, Q&A, text classification, text padding, and generation of code.
Claude 3.5 Sonnet is the latest version of the best LLM model from Anthropic (and the best LLM at the moment).

GPT-3.5 Turbo is OpenAI older language model with wide context window, optimized for chatbots, content generation, and code documentation (cheaper than GPT4 but without multimodal and less smarter than GPT4).
GPT-4o is OpenAI most advanced multimodal model that’s faster and cheaper than GPT-4 Turbo with stronger vision capabilities. The model has 128K context and an October 2023 knowledge cutoff.
GPT-4o mini is OpenAI most cost-efficient small model that’s smarter and cheaper than GPT-3.5 Turbo, and has vision capabilities. The model has 128K context and an October 2023 knowledge cutoff.
